cc:Work.dc:title: Some Title
cc:Work.dc:description: # Ohm's Law This is a simple demo for showing how automatically executing sequences can be added to interactive schematics # Procedure + Create a schematic diagram for Ohm's law in inkscape and label the outputs and inputs. + In this case, I have inserted a text element with text `PV1`, and one with `A1` + In addition, I added a text element for calculating current of the form `EQ:expression`, + set its text to `EQ:A1/1000` + For automatically sweeping the voltage output(PV1) and recording Current(A1/1000) vs Voltage(A1) + Add the sweep parameters to the description field of the element to be varied automatically. + eg, for this experiment, PV1 is to be varied, and A1/1000 to be measured for each point. + The first 3 lines indicate manual sweeping, and the rest will create a button `automatic` inside PV1's popup. + Clicking on the button will launch automatic sweep mode. ``` min=-5 max=5 #Configure Automatic Sweep sweep=PV1 title=A1 vs A1/1000 start=-5 stop=5 stepsize=0.01 delay=1 settling=2 xaxis=A1 xmin=-5 xmax=5 yaxis=A1/1000 ymin=-.005 ymax=.005 ``` When the user taps in the `automatic` button , the following configuration dialog appears that also allows the user to modify parameters before starting the sequence ## Final result After the user initiates the sweep, the parameters automatically follow the prescribed sequence and plot the graph
